e}],"activity_page_count":1,"activity_page_number":1,"summaries":[{"id":17151,"category":"team","content":"The reporter noted that our installation instructions for our [Linux Desktop Client for Fedora](https://help.dropbox.com/installs-integrations/desktop/linux-repository) specified HTTP urls instead of HTTPS. This could allow an attacker, with a privileged network position, the ability to swap the GPG key during installation allowing them to install a rogue signing key on the victim's machine.\n\nWe updated the instructions in our help center to use HTTPS urls.  ","can_view?":true,"can_edit?":false,"content_html":"\u003cp\u003eThe reporter noted that our installation instructions for our \u003ca href=\"/redirect?url=https%3A%2F%2Fhelp.dropbox.com%2Finstalls-integrations%2Fdesktop%2Flinux-repository\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003eLinux Desktop Client for Fedora\u003c/span\u003e\u003ci class=\"icon-external-link\"\u003e\u003c/i\u003e\u003c/a\u003e specified HTTP urls instead of HTTPS. This could allow an attacker, with a privileged network position, the ability to swap the GPG key during installation allowing them to install a rogue signing key on the victim\u0026#39;s machine.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eWe updated the instructions in our help center to use HTTPS urls.  \u003c/p\u003e\n"},{"category":"researcher","can_view?":true,"can_create?":false}]}